---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const post = {
  title: "Notes on Learning",
  description: "What I've learned over years of self-education.",
  pubDate: new Date("2026-04-20"),
  tags: ["learning"]
};
---

<BaseLayout lang="en" title={post.title} description={post.description}>
  <article class="blog-post">
    <header class="post-header">
      <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}`} class="back-link">← Back to main</a>
      <h1 class="post-title">{post.title}</h1>
      <div class="post-meta">
        <time datetime={post.pubDate.toISOString()}>
          {post.pubDate.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}
        </time>
        <div class="post-tags">
          {post.tags.map(tag => <span class="tag">{tag}</span>)}
        </div>
      </div>
      <img src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/blog/hero-learning.svg`} alt="Learning illustration" class="post-hero" />
    </header>

    <div class="post-content">
      <p>Self-education is a skill. Like any skill, it gets better with practice.</p>

      <p>Here's what I've learned after years of teaching myself programming, design, and other things.</p>

      <h2>1. Learn by building</h2>

      <p>Tutorials are useful for syntax. But real learning happens when you build something without a guide.</p>

      <p>The moment you get stuck and have to figure it out yourself — that's when you actually learn.</p>

      <h2>2. Small, consistent effort beats bursts</h2>

      <p>30 minutes every day is better than 5 hours once a week.</p>

      <p>Consistency builds momentum. Bursts burn you out.</p>

      <h2>3. Teach to learn</h2>

      <p>If you can't explain it simply, you don't understand it well enough.</p>

      <p>Writing blog posts, answering questions, or just explaining concepts to yourself forces you to clarify your thinking.</p>

      <h2>4. Focus on fundamentals</h2>

      <p>Frameworks change. Fundamentals don't.</p>

      <p>Learn how things work under the hood. The rest is just syntax.</p>

      <h2>5. Don't wait to feel ready</h2>

      <p>You'll never feel ready. Start anyway.</p>

      <p>The best time to start was yesterday. The second best time is now.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
